irector entirely.[2C[2BI verified nginx runs as [38;2;177;185;249mwww-data[39m and [38;2;177;185;249m/var/www/html/.well-known/acme-challenge/[83G[39mis wor[90Gd-traver[99Gable, so this s[115Grves[2C[1Bcleanly. Both[17Gtarget stri[30Gs[32Gappear exactly[47Gonce,[53Gso[56Gthe[60Gregexes[68Gare[72Gunambiguous.[2C[1B[K[2C[1BI did [1mnot[22m touch any files. Here is the proposed diff:[K[2C[2B[32m--- a/chatmail/roles/security/tasks/main.yml[39m[K[2C[1B[32m+++ b/chatmail/roles/security/tasks/main.yml[39m[K[2C[1B[90m@@ -219,3 +219,73 @@[2C[1B[39m [5G   sed -i '/location \/ {/a\\t\t\[39Gauth_basic "Private[59GServer";\n\t\t\tauth_basic_user_file[96G/etc/nginx/.htpasswd;'[2C[1B/etc/nginx/nginx.conf[2C[1B   when: auth_basic_check.rc != 0[K[2C[1B   notify: reload nginx[K[2C[1B   tags: [security, basicauth][2C[1B[32m+[8G[39m[K[2C[1B[32m+# --- ACME / Let's Encrypt HTTP-01 renewal fix (post-cmdeploy) ---[2C[1B+#[6G[39m[K[2C[1B[32m+# cmdeploy regenerates /etc/nginx/nginx.conf on every `cmdeploy run` with an[2C[1B+# :80 block that puts `return 301 https://...` in the SERVER context:[3C[1B#[5C[1B   [10Gserver[17G{[39m[K[4C[1B[32m         listen 80;[39m[40;1H[38;3H[?25h[?25l[H[3G[K[2C[1B[1mRecommended fix — your Option C, corrected[22m[K[2C[1B[K[2C[1BOne idempotent[18Gnginx.conf patch in[38Gthe[42G[1msecurity role[56G[22m(runs[62Gafter[68Gdeploy;[76Gre-applies[87Gafter[93Gevery[99G[38;2;177;185;249mcmdeploy run[39m):[2C[2B1. [1mMov[10G [38;2;177;185;249mreturn 301[39m into [38;2;177;185;249mlocation /[22m[39m → it now[47Gruns[52Gin[55Gthe[59G[3mlocation[23m-rewrite[76Gphase,[83Gafter[89Glocation[98Gselection,[109Gso[112Gthe[2C[1Bmore-specific[17Gacme-challenge[32Glocation[41Gwins.[2C[1B2. [1mServe the challenge from the webroot[22m ([38;2;177;185;249mroot /var/www/html;[39m) inst[70Gad of[76G[38;2;177;185;249mproxy_pass http://acmetool;[39m → matches[2C[1Bacmetool's[14Gconfigured[25G[38;2;177;185;249mwebroot-paths[39G[39mexactly,[48Gand[52Gremoves[60Gthe[64Gdependency[75Gon[78Gthe[82Gbroken[89G:402[94Gredirector[105Gentirely.[2C[1B[K[2C[1BI v[7Grified nginx runs as [38;2;177;185;249mwww-data[39m and[41G[38;2;177;185;249m/var/www/html/.well-known/acme-challenge/[83G[39mis[86Gworld-traversable,[105Gso[108Gthis[113Gserves[2C[1Bcleanly. Both target strings appear exactly once, so the regexes are unambiguous.[K[2C[1B[K[2C[1BI[5Gdid[9G[1mnot[13G[22mtouch[19Gany[23Gfiles.[30GHere[35Gis[38Gthe[42Gproposed[51Gdiff:[2C[1B[K[2C[1B[32m--- a/chatmail/roles/security/tasks/main.yml[39m[K[2C[1B[32m+++ b/chatmail/roles/security/tasks/main.yml[2C[1B[90m@@ -219,3 +219,73 @@[39m[K[7C[1Bsed[12G-i[15G'/location[26G\/[29G{/a\\t\t\tauth_basic[50G"Private[59GServer";\n\t\t\tauth_basic_user_file[96G/etc/nginx/.htpasswd;'[2C[1B/etc/nginx/nginx.conf[K[2C[1B   when: auth_basic_check.rc != 0[K[2C[1B   notify: reload nginx[5C[1Btags:[12G[security, basicauth][K[2C[1B[32m+[39m[K[2C[1B[32m+# --- ACME / Let's Encrypt HTTP-01 renewal fix (post-cmdeploy) ---[2C[1B+#[6G[39m[K[2C[1B[32m+# cmdeploy regenerates /etc/nginx/nginx.conf on every `cmdeploy run` with an[3C[1B# :80 block that puts `return 301 https://...` in the SERVER context:[4C[1B[39m[K[4C[1B[32m     server {[5C[1B        list[20G 80;[39m[K[5C[1B[32m   [10G    location /.well-known/acme-challenge/ {[54Gproxy_pass[65Ghttp://acmetool; }[4C[1B         return 301 https://$host$request_uri;      # <-- server context[9C[1B}[39m[K[4C[1B[K[40;1H[38;3H[?25h]0;⠐ Fix Let's Encrypt certificate renewal on Delta server[?25l[H[2C[1BOne idempotent nginx.conf patch in the [1ms[44Gcurity role[56G[22m(runs[62Gafter[68Gdeploy;[76Gre-applies[87Gafter[93Gevery[99G[38;2;177;185;249mcmdeploy run[39m):[2C[2B1. [1mMove [38;2;177;185;249mreturn 301[39m into [38;2;177;185;249mlocation /[38G[22m[39m→ it now runs in the [3mlocation[23m-r[70Gwrite[76Gphase, after location selection, so the[2C[1Bmore-specific[17Gacme-challenge[32Glocation[41Gwins.[2C[1B2[6G[1mServe the challenge from the webroot[43G[22m([38;2;177;185;249mroot /var/www/html;[39m) inst[70Gad of[76G[38;2;177;185;249mproxy_pass http://acmetool;[39m → matches[K[2C[1Bacm[7Gtool's configured [38;2;177;185;249mwebroot-paths[39m exactly,[48Gand[52Gremoves[60Gthe[64Gdependency[75Gon[78Gthe[82Gbroken[89G:402[94Gredirector[105Gentirely.[2C[1B[K[2C[1BI v[7Grified[14Gnginx runs[25Gas [38;2;177;185;249mwww-data[39m and [38;2;177;185;249m/var/www/html/.well-known/acme-challenge/[39m is world-traversable,[105Gso this serves[2C[1Bcleanly.[12GBoth[17Gtarget[24Gstrings[32Gappear[39Gexactly[47Gonce,[53Gso[56Gthe[60Gregexes[68Gare[72Gunambiguous.[2C[1B[K[2C[1BI did [1mnot[22m touch any files. Here is the proposed diff:[K[2C[2B[32m--- a/chatmail/roles/security/tasks/main.yml[39m[K[2C[1B[32m+++ b/chatmail/roles/security/tasks/main.yml[2C[1B[90m@@ -219,3 +219,73 @@[39m[K[2C[1B     sed -i '/location \/ {/a\\t\t\tauth_basic[50G"Private[59GServer";\n\t\t\tauth_basic_user_file[96G/etc/nginx/.htpasswd;'[2C[1B/etc/nginx/nginx.conf[5C[1Bwhen:[12Gauth_basic_check.rc != 0[K[2C[1B   notify: reload nginx[5C[1Btags[12G[security, basicauth][K[2C[1B[32m+[6G[39m[K[2C[1B[32m+# --- ACME / Let's Encrypt HTTP-01 renewal fix (post-cmdeploy) ---[3C[1B#[5C[1Bcmdeploy[15Greg[19Gnerates /e[30Gc/nginx/ngi[42Gx.con[48G on every `cmdeploy run` with an[4C[1B :80 block that puts `return 301 https://...` in the SERVER context:[4C[1B[39m[K[5C[1B[32m   [10Gserver {[39m[K[4C[1B[32m         listen 80;[9C[1B    location /.well-known/acme-challenge/ { proxy_pass http://acmetool; }[13C[1Bretur[21G3[23G1 https://$host$request_uri;      # <-- server context[9C[1B}[39m[K[4C[1B[K[5C[1B[32mnginx runs a server-context `return` in the server-rewrite phase, BEFORE it[4C[1B selects a location, so EVERY :80 request (incl. /.well-known/acme-challenge/)[39m[40;1H[38;3H[?25h[?25l[H[3GOne[7Gidempotent[18Gnginx.conf[29Gpatch[35Gin[38Gthe[42G[1msecurity role[56G[22m(runs[62Gafter[68Gdeploy;[76Gre-applies[87Gafter[93Gevery[99G[38;2;177;185;249mcmdeploy run[39m):[2C[1B[K[2C[1B1.[6G[1mMove [38;2;177;185;249mreturn 301[39m into [38;2;177;185;249mlocation /[38G[22m[39m→[40Git[43Gnow[47Gruns[52Gin[55Gthe[59G[3mlocation[23m-rewrite[76Gphase,[83Gafter[89Glocation[98Gselection,[109Gso[112Gthe[2C[1Bmore-specific acme-challenge location wi[44Gs.[47G[K[2C[1B2. [1mServe the challenge from the webroot[22m ([38;2;177;185;249mroot /var/www/html;[39m)[65Ginstead[73Gof[76G[38;2;177;185;249mproxy_pass http://acmetool;[104G[39m→[106Gmatches[2C[1Bacmetool's configured [38;2;177;185;249mwebroot-paths[39m exactly, and removes the dependency on the broken :402 redirector entirely.[2C[1B[K[2C[1BI[5Gverified[14Gnginx[20Gruns[25Gas[28G[38;2;177;185;249mwww-data[37G[39mand[41G[38;2;177;185;249m/var/www/html/.well-known/acme-challenge/[83G[39mis[86Gworld-traversable,[105Gso[108Gthis[113Gserves[2C[1Bcleanly. Both target strings appear exactly once, so the regexes are unambiguous.[K[2C[1B[K[2C[1BI[5Gdid[9G[1mnot[13G[22mtouch[19Gany[23Gfiles.[30GHere[35Gis[38Gthe[42Gproposed[51Gdiff:[2C[1B[K[2C[1B[32m--- a/chatmail/roles/security/tasks/main.yml[2C[1B+++[7Gb[2C[1B[90m@@ -219,3 +219,73 @@[39m[K[2C[1B     sed -i '/location[26G\/[29G{/a\\t\t\tauth_basic[50G"Private[59GServer";\n\t\t\tauth_basic_user_file[96G/etc/nginx/.htpasswd;'[2C[1B/etc/nginx/nginx.conf[K[2C[1B   when: auth_basic_check.rc[32G!=[35G0[5C[1Bnotify: relo[19Gd nginx[K[5C[1Btags: [security, basicauth][2C[1B[32m+[6G[39m[K[3C[1B[32m# --- ACME / Let's Encrypt HTTP-01 renewal fix (post-cmdeploy) ---[4C[1B[39m[K[4C[1B[32m cmdeploy regenerates /etc/nginx/nginx.conf on every `cmdeploy run` with an[5C[1B:80 b[13Gck that pu[24Gs `r[30Gur[33G 301 https://...` in the[58GSERVER context:[39m[K[4C[1B[K[4C[1B[32m     server {[9C[1B    listen 80;[14C[1Bocation /.well-known/acme-challenge/ { proxy_pass http://acmetool; }[13C[1Breturn 301 https://$host$request_uri;[52G [54G   # <-- [64Gerver contex[77G[39m[K[9C[1B[32m}[39m[K[4C[1B[K[4C[1B[32m nginx runs a server-context `return` in the server-rewrite phase, BEFORE it[5C[1Bselects a location, s[28G EVERY :80 [40Gequest (incl. /.well-known/[68Gcme-challenge/)[5C[1Bis 301-redirec[21Ged and the challeng[41G locatio[50G is[54Gnev[58Gr reached. acmetoo[77G's[39m[K[40;1H[38;3H[?25h]0;⠂ Fix Let's Encrypt certificate renewal on Delta server[?25l[H[3Gmore-specific acme-challenge location wins.[K[2C[1B2.[6G[1mServe the challenge from the webroot[43G[22m([38;2;177;185;249mroot /var/www/html;[39m)[65Ginstead[73Gof[76G[38;2;177;185;249mproxy_pass http://acmetool;[104G[39m→[106Gmatches[2C[1Bacmetool's configured [38;2;177;185;249mwebroot-paths[39m exactly, a[50Gd[52Gremov[58Gs the dependency on th[81G brok[87Gn[89G:402 redir[100Gctor e[107Gtirely.[K[2C[1B[K[2C[1BI verified nginx runs as [38;2;177;185;249mwww-data[39m and [38;2;177;185;249m/va[45G/www[50Ghtml/.[57Gell-known/acme-challenge/[39m is world-traversable, so [109Ghis serves[2C[1Bcleanly. Both target strings appear[46G once, so the[60Gregex[66Gs ar[71G unambiguous.[K[4C[2Bdid [1mnot[22m touch any files. Here is the proposed diff:[K[2C[1B[K[2C[1B[32m--- a/chatmail/roles/security/tasks/main.yml[2C[1B+++ b/chatmail/roles/security/tasks/main.yml[39m[K[2C[1B[90m@@ -219,3 +219,73 @@[2C[1B[39m     sed -i '/location \/ {/a\\t\t\tauth_basic[50G"Private[59GServer";\n\t\t\tauth_basic_user_file[96G/etc/nginx/.htpasswd;'[2C[1B/etc/nginx/nginx.conf[K[2C[1B   when: auth_basic_check.rc[32G!=[35G0[5C[1Bnotify: reload ngi[25Gx[K[2C[1B   tags: [security, basicauth][2C[1B[32m+[6G[39m[K[2C[1B[32m+# --- ACME / Let's Encrypt HTTP-01 renewal fix (post-cmdeploy) ---[2C[1B+#[6G[39m[K[3C[1B[32m# cmdeploy regenerates /etc/nginx/nginx.conf on every `cmdeploy run` with an[5C[1B:80[10Gblock tha[20G puts `re[30Gurn 301 https://...`[51Gin the SERVER context:[5C[2B    serve[16G {[39m[K[5C[1B[32m   [10G    listen[21G80;[39m[K[4C[1B[32m         location /.well-known/acme-challenge/ { proxy_pass http://acmetool; }[9C[1B    return 301 https://$host$request_uri;      # <-- server context[9C[1B}[39m[K[4C[1B[K[5C[1B[32mnginx[12Gruns a server-context `re[38Gu[40Gn` in the server-rewrite phase, BEFORE it[5C[1Bselects a location, so EVERY :80 request (incl. /.well-known/acme-challenge/)[4C[1B is 301-redirected and the challenge location is never reached. acmetool's[5C[1BHTTP-01 self-t[21Gst then s[31Ges[34Ga non-200 and ren[52Gwal fails on[65Gall SANs.[39m[K[4C[1B[K[5C[1B[32macmetool answers via WEBROOT, not the :402 redirecto[59G[39m[K[40;1H[38;3H[?25h[?25l[H[3G2. [1mServe the challenge from the webroot[22m ([38;2;177;185;249mroot /var/www/html;[39m)[65Ginstead[73Gof[76G[38;2;177;185;249mproxy_pass http://acmetool;[104G[39m→[106Gmatches[2C[1Bacmetool's configured [38;2;177;185;249mwebroot-paths[39m exactly, and removes the dependency on the broken :402 redirector entirely.[2C[1B[K[2C[1BI[5Gverified[14Gnginx[20Gruns[25Gas[28G[38;2;177;185;249mwww-data[37G[39mand[41G[38;2;177;185;249m/var/www/html/.well-known/acme-challenge/[83G[39mis[86Gworld-traversable,[105Gso[108Gthis[113Gserves[2C[1Bcleanly. Both target strings appear exactly once, so the regexes are unambiguous.[K[2C[1B[K[2C[1BI[5Gdid[9G[1mnot[13G[22mtouch[19Gany[23Gfiles.[30GHere[35Gis[38Gthe[42Gproposed[51Gdiff:[2C[1B[K[2C[1B[32m--- a/chatmail/roles/security/tasks/main.yml[2C[1B+++[7Gb[2C[1B[90m@@ -219,3 +219,73 @@[39m[K[2C[1B     sed -i '/location[26G\/[29G{/a\\t\t\tauth_basic[50G"Private[59GServer";\n\t\t\tauth_basic_user_file[96G/etc/nginx/.htpasswd;'[2C[1B/etc/nginx/nginx.conf[K[2C[1B   when: auth_basic_check.rc[32G!=[35G0[5C[1Bnotify: relo[19Gd nginx[K[5C[1Btags: [security, basicauth][2C[1B[32m+[6G[39m[K[3C[1B[32m# --- ACME / Let's Encrypt HTTP-01 renewal fix (post-cmdeploy) ---[4C[1B[39m[K[4C[1B[32m cmdeploy regenerates /etc/nginx/nginx.conf on every `cmdeploy run` with an[5C[1B:80 b[13Gck that pu[24Gs `r[30Gur[33G 301 https://...` in the[58GSERVER context:[39m[K[4C[1B[K[4C[1B[32m     server {[9C[1B    listen 80;[14C[1Bocation /.well-known/acme-challenge/ { proxy_pass http://acmetool; }[13C[1Breturn 301 https://$host$request_uri;[52G [54G   # <-- [64Gerver contex[77G[39m[K[9C[1B[32m}[39m[K[4C[1B[K[4C[1B[32m nginx runs a server-context `return` in the server-rewrite phase, BEFORE it[5C[1Bselects a location, s[28G EVERY :80 [40Gequest (incl. /.well-known/[68Gcme-challenge/)[5C[1Bis 301-redirec[21Ged and the challeng[41G locatio[50G is[54Gnev[58Gr reached. acmetoo[77G's[39m[K[5C[1B[32mHTTP-01 self-test[24Gthen s[31Ges [35G no[39G-200 and renewal fails on all[69GSANs.[39m[K[4C[1B[K[4C[1B[32m acmetool answers via WEBROOT, not the :402 redirector[5C[1B(/var/lib/acm[20G/conf/target ->[36Gwebroot-paths: /var/www/html/.well-known/acme-challenge),[39m[40;1H[38;3H[?25h]0;⠐ Fix Let's Encrypt certificate renewal on Delta server[?25l[H[3GI verified nginx runs as [38;2;177;185;249mwww-data[39m and [38;2;177;185;249m/va[45G/www[50Ghtml/.[