empotent: guarded on the[33Gcmdeploy-generated `p[55Goxy_pass http://acmetool;`,[39m[K[40;1H[38;3H[?25h[?25l[H[5Gdid [1mnot[22m touch any files. Here is the proposed diff:[K[2C[1B[K[2C[1B[32m--- a/chatmail/roles/security/tasks/main.yml[2C[1B+++ b/chatmail/roles/security/tasks/main.yml[39m[K[2C[1B[90m@@ -219,3 +219,73 @@[2C[1B[39m     sed -i '/location \/ {/a\\t\t\tauth_basic[50G"Private[59GServer";\n\t\t\tauth_basic_user_file[96G/etc/nginx/.htpasswd;'[2C[1B/etc/nginx/nginx.conf[K[2C[1B   when: auth_basic_check.rc[32G!=[35G0[5C[1Bnotify: reload ngi[25Gx[K[2C[1B   tags: [security, basicauth][2C[1B[32m+[6G[39m[K[2C[1B[32m+# --- ACME / Let's Encrypt HTTP-01 renewal fix (post-cmdeploy) ---[2C[1B+#[6G[39m[K[3C[1B[32m# cmdeploy regenerates /etc/nginx/nginx.conf on every `cmdeploy run` with an[5C[1B:80[10Gblock tha[20G puts `re[30Gurn 301 https://...`[51Gin the SERVER context:[5C[2B    serve[16G {[39m[K[5C[1B[32m   [10G    listen[21G80;[39m[K[4C[1B[32m         location /.well-known/acme-challenge/ { proxy_pass http://acmetool; }[9C[1B    return 301 https://$host$request_uri;      # <-- server context[9C[1B}[39m[K[4C[1B[K[5C[1B[32mnginx[12Gruns a server-context `re[38Gu[40Gn` in the server-rewrite phase, BEFORE it[5C[1Bselects a location, so EVERY :80 request (incl. /.well-known/acme-challenge/)[4C[1B is 301-redirected and the challenge location is never reached. acmetool's[5C[1BHTTP-01 self-t[21Gst then s[31Ges[34Ga non-200 and ren[52Gwal fails on[65Gall SANs.[39m[K[4C[1B[K[5C[1B[32macmetool answers via WEBROOT, not the :402 redirecto[59G[39m[K[5C[1B[32m(/var/lib/acme/conf/targ[31Gt ->[36Gwebroot-paths: /v[54Gr/www/html/.well-known/acme-challenge),[4C[1B so we serve the challenge straight from that dir and drop the proxy_pass.[4C[1B[39m[K[5C[1B[32mIdempotent: guarded on the[33Gcmdeploy-generated `p[55Goxy_pass