d drop the proxy_pass.[4C[1B[39m[K[5C[1B[32mIdempot[14Gnt:[18Gguarded on the cmdeploy-generated `proxy_pass[64Ghttp://acmetool;`,[4C[1B which reappears after every deploy and is gone once we patch.[3C[1B[39m[K[3C[1B[32m-[6Gname:[12GD[14Gtect unp[23Gtched cmdeploy acme-challeng[53Gblock[39m[K[3C[1B[32m  command: grep -qF 'proxy_pass http://acmetool;' /etc/nginx/nginx.conf[3C[1B [6Gregister: acme_nginx_unpatched[39m[K[40;1H[38;3H[?25h[?25l[H[3G/etc/nginx/nginx.conf[K[2C[1B   when: auth_basic_check.rc != 0[K[2C[1B   notify: reload nginx[5C[1Btags:[12G[security, basicauth][K[2C[1B[32m+[39m[K[2C[1B[32m+# --- ACME / Let's Encrypt HTTP-01 renewal fix (post-cmdeploy) ---[2C[1B+#[6G[39m[K[2C[1B[32m+# cmdeploy regenerates /etc/nginx/nginx.conf on every `cmdeploy run` with an[3C[1B# :80 block that puts `return 301 https://...` in the SERVER context:[4C[1B[39m[K[4C[1B[32m     server {[5C[1B        list[20G 80;[39m[K[5C[1B[32m   [10G    location /.well-known/acme-challenge/ {[54Gproxy_pass[65Ghttp://acmetool; }[4C[1B         return 301 https://$host$request_uri;      # <-- server context[9C[1B}[39m[K[4C[1B[K[5C[1B[32mnginx[12Gruns [18G server-context `return` in the serve[56G-rewrite[65Gphase, BEFORE it[39m[K[5C[1B[32mselects[14Ga location, so EVERY :80 [46G (incl.[54G/.well[61Gknown/acme-challenge/)[5C[1Bis[9G301-redirected and the challenge location is never reached. acmetool's[4C[1B HTTP-01 self-test then sees a non-200 and renewal fails on all SANs.[4C[1B[39m[K[5C[1B[32macm[10Gtool answers via WEBROOT, not the :402 redirector[39m[K[5C[1B[32m(/var/lib/acme/conf/targ[31Gt -> w[38Gbroot-p[47Ghs:[51G/var/www/html/.well-known/acme-challenge),[5C[1Bso we serve th[21G challeng[31G [33Gtraight from that dir and drop the proxy_pass.[5C[2BIdemp[12Gtent: guarded on the cmdeploy-generated `proxy_pass http://acmetool;`